This paper deals with colorization of grayscale images using generative adversarial networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of conditional GANs and convolutional networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of stride 1 to maintain spatial information, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
